-- Dubai May Defer, Cancel $29 Billion of Airbus, Boeing Jet Orders, WSJ Says
-- Alan Purkiss
-- 2010-06-29T06:10:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/dubai-may-cancel-airbus-boeing-plane-orders-wall-street-journal-reports.html

          
          
             Dubai Aerospace Enterprise may defer
or cancel $29 billion of orders for 200 aircraft, divided 
equally between Airbus SAS and Boeing Co., the Wall Street 
Journal reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the 
matter.   
 As an alternative, the state-controlled Dubai 
aircraft-leasing company may try to switch the orders to 
Emirates Airline and FlyDubai, the newspaper said.  
 The cancelation threat stems from Dubaiâ€™s parlous financial
state, the Journal said, adding that Dubai Aerospace, Airbus 
and Boeing all declined to comment.   
